sbol:ComponentDefinition.addgene:growthInstructions: On transformation of E. coli with normal protocols, colonies take longer to form and are very small. If you have trouble growing the bugs, pick a few colonies and grow at 37°C, 220rpm in 5ml aliquots of LB + Kanamycin (half-strength). If there is little growth after 18-24 h, re-seed 0.5 ml of the culture into a fresh 5 ml aliquot of LB + kanamycin (half-strength). Grow at 37 °C, 220 rpm. Repeat if necessary. Larger volumes can be obtained by normal protocols.
